Yes. I was referring to SkyTab.

Card Connect is a mess and so desperately needs to be combined with a company that has better
technology.

The current First Data / Card Connect technology plan, known as “Bolt” to the outside world, does not
look promising.

From what I have heard, their P2PE solution, the one they are out selling now, is provided by Bluefin and
only supports lngenico devices.

Their semi-integrated product (Bolt) currently routes all transactions through “123” and does not support
EMV. Their plan to to get EMV certified with First Data, which everyone knows is a nightmare. The one thing
that could save them would be a Rapid Connect certification but I haven’t heard this is even being
considered.

Also, another interesting challenge is the rumored First Data deployment of Clover. Clover is their own
product and competes directly with Card Connect.

I think combining Shift4 and Card Connect would both improve the Card Connect product as well as
allow Shift4 to enter new verticals.

Subject: RE: Card Connect / First Data

Hey Taylor,

We are building the SkyTab Mobile device. The plan is for it be semi-integrated (connects on the local
network or via the cloud through web sockets) and we do have an SDK. The SDK is currently available
for C#, .NET, Java, Javascript.

Internally, we are calling the device "LVX Mobile". LVX stands for Lighthouse (our cloud-based business
management system) Venmo (consumer engagement) Xcelerator (our boarding tool).

When we purchased the assets of BarFly, their previous device was named "SkyTab". We did not intend
keep the name, but it is starting to grow on us.

The device accepts MSR, EMV, NFC an features PIN on glass. The processor certifications are complete,
it's just the POS applications that need to be completed now.

Regarding an introduction to Card Connect, I spoke with Jared and he wants to see the outcome of the
Stratgic Review process before reaching out. I understand there is no need to rush this either. I wanted to
make the intro.

Let me know if you have any questions about SkyTab-

Thanks,
j.D.
